    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Every time when we try to schedule up some operations, a new signal receiver `interrupt` will be allocated.\r\nAnd the signal is only passed by the **this** pointer to the relevant operations.\r\n\r\nSo in this case, the `s` is only passed to some old operations and then the `interrupt` is for the new operations. ",
